    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102751</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Diego is making personal cheese pizzas for his party. On each pizza, the ratio of tablespoons of parmesan to tablespoons of mozzarella is 2 to 5.&#xA0;</p>

<table border="1">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col">number of pizzas</th>
			<th scope="col">tablespoons of parmesan</th>
			<th scope="col">tablespoons of mozzarella</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>1</td>
			<td>2</td>
			<td>5</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>6</td>
			<td>12</td>
			<td>30</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>8</td>
			<td></td>
			<td></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>15</td>
			<td></td>
			<td></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<ol>
	<li>Complete the table to show how much of each type of cheese will be needed for different numbers of pizzas.</li>
	<li>How much <em>more</em> mozzarella than parmesan is needed if he makes 8 pizzas?</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>For 8 pizzas: 16, 40. For 15 pizzas: 30, 75.</li>
	<li>24 tablespoons, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47628">\(40-16=24\)</span>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
